            "body": "`__builtin_constant_p()` is a compiler extension that may or may not be available. I searched a bit and it seems that C compilers tend to support it but can disagree about what is a constant and when they are recognised as such (`-O0` disables that on GCC, for example). If Cython knows that we're dividing by a constant, why not make sure that's taken into account?",
